          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>12325</commentid>
            <who name="Martin Wittemann">martin.wittemann</who>
            <bug_when>2009-09-15 16:28:29 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Currently, the generator can not handle - (minus) in class names and fails to run with a misleading error message:
!!! Detected conflict between filename and classname!
!!! Classname: interfaces.I1_1
!!! Path: interfaces/I1_1-1.js
The generator posts something which is not true and no end user can get the the source of the error with this error message.
Perhaps the generator should accept - in class names or at least offer some good error message that the user knows what&#39;s wrong.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>12330</commentid>
            <who name="Thomas Herchenroeder">thron7</who>
            <bug_when>2009-09-15 17:53:53 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Hyphens (-) cannot be part of a class name, as a qooxdoo class name has to be a 
valid Javascript identifier, and a hyphen is not a valid character in 
Javascript identifiers (see this bug#2429).

But there should definitely be a better error message, so keeping the bug open 
for this.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
